description: Recently sold: $312,200. If you are tired of seeing the same old rambler plan, you will be thrilled with this expanded home!  The eat in kitchen is now a perfect gathering place with it's 16 x 19 size, center island, lots of natural light & walk out to deck. There is an abundance of cabinets, planning desk & steps from the garage!  There is also informal dining (walkout!) adjacent to livingroom & kitchen.  3 bedrooms on one level.  Upper level 3/4 bath has a walk thru to the owner's suite.  Lower level is an entry door walkout complete w/4th bedroom, full bath, family room with gas burning fireplace for our gelid winter, a nice sized office w/plenty of built in cabinets, & an 8 x 14 storage room.  The 4th bedroom also has a small seating area. Great panoramic views from both kitchen & the deck to open space & beyond.  You will enjoy the oversize yard.  So - this is not at all your typical rambler & in the heart of Battle Creek, it is a rare find.  Make plans to come see this home today before it is too late!!

description:
Recently sold: $210,000. Welcome to 2061 Case Avenue! Stepping through the front door the spacious living room invites you in with coved ceilings, abundant windows, and a fantastic area to relax after a long day or host movie nights in.

The adjacent dining room is large enough to host holiday celebrations and intimate gatherings alike with friends and family! Head through the pocket door for easy movement between this space and the kitchen. Enjoy views across the front yard to witness the changing Minnesota seasons.

The home?s kitchen lays claim to granite countertops, glass tiled backsplash, and abundant cabinetry. Cooking will be a breeze thanks to plenty of space to prepare your favorite recipes. 

Around the corner you will find two main floor bedrooms occupying each back corner of the home as well as the home?s full bathroom. Each bedroom boasts generous storage and fantastic daylight with views across the large backyard!

Travel to the upper level to find a third bedroom with a large closet. Along the hallway sits a family room which can also be utilized as a home office, playroom, or library. Let your imagination transform this space!

Store your belongings with ease in the lower level where you will also find a washer and dryer. The backyard is fully fenced meaning your four legged family members can explore worry-free! Put your green thumb to use thanks to all-day sunlight which will allow garden beds to flourish. This is also a perfect spot for hosting barbecues, yard game tournaments, or to create a bonfire pit for roasting s?mores.

A great location with nearby parks, easy access to highways, as well as local shops and restaurants. Don?t miss the chance to call this home!

description:
Recently sold: $195,000. This home boasts large functional rooms with the character that exemplifies the period in which it was constructed.  Built in 1913 and meticulously maintained; gleaming hardwood floors, formal/informal dining areas, double lot, and many newer windows are just a few of the pluses this home has to offer.  Perfect for either those who entertain or your growing family.  Private/fully fenced yard is extensively landscaped with patio area and ample space for play.
Situated right across the street from a park and playground sits this wonderfully updated and maintained 1 1/2 story. Inviting front porch, 2 living areas, eat-in kitchen, formal dining, and newer 2 car garage plus so much more. Situated atop a hill affords one some serenity while being in the heart of St. Paul. Quick access into both Downtowns as well as easy access to shopping along White Bear Ave and Maplewood Mall.

description: Recently sold: $190,000. Adorable St. Paul Bungalow with charming curb appeal. You will love the beautiful hardwood floors on the main floor. The spacious living room has a two large windows allowing great natural light into the house. There are two nice sized bedrooms on the main floor and a very spacious bedroom in the upper level. There are so many updates!!! Including a new roof in 2018, and HVAC in 2015. The fenced private back yard is the perfect place to relax, lay out in the sun, or read a book. There is a full basement with 384 finished square feet and a 17 x 10 space to use for crafting, storage, or a home gym. The property is only 5 miles NE of downtown St. Paul. This location is near Lake Phalen, Beaver Lake, Golf courses,  3M, and all of the great restaurants in St. Paul. This property would make a fantastic owner occupied home or investment. It is move in ready. Call today for a showing!

description: Recently sold: $181,000. WOW! Don't miss this one. Large, totally updated home next to Beaver Lake. Home has more updates than can be listed. Exterior has great curb appeal with low maintenance brick and vinyl. Main level has open floor plan with a beautiful fireplace in the living room. Kitchen has all the updates and a large center island. Patio door off kitchen leads to the beautiful backyard. There is a main level bedroom and full bathroom. Upper level has two large bedrooms and another full bathroom. There is also plenty of storage space. Two car garage is attached with a mud room where you could put a main level laundry. Basement has large open family room.

Recently sold: $212,000. Fully & professionally renovated mid-century home located on a quiet, non-through street, just steps away from Furness Trail & Hayden Heights Playground. Walk in & immediately see its modern colors & trendy finishes. The southern exposure allows light to pour in the front picture window. As you make your way through the home, you will find everything brand new from the carpet, luxury vinyl tile floors, trim, light fixtures & fresh paint. The wider style galley kitchen is all new with stainless steel appliances, granite countertops, beautiful crown molding & subway tile backsplash. The larger foundation size creates space for all 3 bedrooms & a true dining area on the main level. The lower level has high ceilings making it perfect for building equity by finishing this space. Brand new roof, furnace, A/C, water heater, windows, garage door, & exterior doors, give you peace of mind. The large backyard is private & partially fenced in.

description: Recently sold: $390,000. Just the right size rambler, custom built for today's downsized,relaxed lifestyle.  No walls separate the living, dining and kitchen areas making it easy to carry on conversations with family and guests. Beautiful main floor master suite with fresh paint, new carpet, walk-in closet, spa like bath with whirlpool tub, walk-in shower and double vanity. Two bedrooms, full bath and a large family room with lovely views of the backyard are on the look out lower level, ideal for kids or guests. Y'all come front porch for chats with neighbors and a "staycation" backyard with a large deck and paver fire pit, it's like going to the cabin without the drive.  Heated, insulated garage with workshop and great storage.  South Maplewood is so pretty with it's rolling hills and mature trees, parks and trails. Minutes from Woobury's shops and restaurants, 3M and easy access to 494, 94 and 61 make living here so convenient without being hectic. Flexible sellers can accommodate a quick closing.
